==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clownish
<hw>Clown"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or resembling a clown, or
characteristic of a clown; ungainly; awkward.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Clownish</xex> hands.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Spenser.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧<qex>Clownish</qex> mimic.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Prior.</au></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Clown"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Coarse; rough; clumsy; awkward; ungainly; rude;
uncivil; ill-bred; boorish; rustic; untutored.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clownishness</ent>⟦br⟧
